When I first posted skin, I wasn't sure if I should have &quot;Custom Image&quot; showing as an option, <br />as it might be difficult for people to make their own background image.<br /><br />Changed my mind. Maybe a few users want to try it.<br />It's the same skin, just a little sign &quot;;&quot; was removed from line 285, using Resource Hacker.<br /><br />I put some tile patterns to switch out in a zip. <br />Then you can make your own. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br /><br />EDIT: I threw in some Windows 95 tiles in folder in Zip<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sun Oct 30, 2016 4:16 pm</p><hr />
