<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7025&amp;p=30127#p30127"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Experiment:  CLASETRO   [7style]]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7025&amp;p=30127#p30127"><![CDATA[
Inspired by Homer Simpson's snazzy car design, minus the tail fins.<br /><br />I took the &quot;Windows 8&quot; skin, added very transparent classic 3d buttons, split dark mode, <br />part &quot;Clear Sharp&quot;, a small set of Metro accent colors, <br />and some sun beams (reflection bands).<br /><br />Ended up with...CLASETRO <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br />It uses some Metro colors, so definitely won't work on Win7 operating system. <br /><br />Really made it for Win10<br /><br />Only works partially on Win8, because system lacks blur menu glass facility.<br />Could always install free trial Big Muscle for menu glass blur.<br />Also there isn't the matching Metro accent colors. I put in substitute Metro colors. <br /><br />Thanks Saijin_Naib. <br />I used 2 background patterns from <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.msfn.org/board/topic/173360-aeroglass-reflection-images/">http://www.msfn.org/board/topic/173360- ... on-images/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Thanks also to Funky Monkey for Hash dots.<br /><br />I can't remember where I got the Aero reflections from. Too many downloads. <br />The original WIN7 one was too blurry. They all got modified anyway to fit menu.<br /><br /><br />Edit: Added the other two views of menu look and added Custom Image option back in.<br />Edit: Minor update to fix pattern mask edge. <br /><br />Time to get back to my electronic projects. Bye <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Fri Oct 28, 2016 6:51 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
